sub_title: Policy officer at Dutch Ministry of Foreign Affairs
summary:
As a Global Law student, my knowledge of the law transcends the traditional boundaries of a single national legal system. More so, attention is paid to a variety of legal systems and the way in which law is globalizing by ways of harmonization and transnationalization. I am interested personally in financial technology and financial regulation, as well as blockchain technology and entrepreneurship.

Currently, I am also looking for an summer internship preferably in one of my areas of interest. I seek to combine my Global Law LLB with courses of the Dutch Law program to obtain Dutch bar membership (civiel effect).

I am arduous, social and ambitious, and I enjoy listening to jazz music and being active as a student in Magister JFT, the Tilburg Law School faculty association. I am also privileged to be in the Outreaching Honors program of Tilburg University.

Do not hesitate to contact me by connecting on LinkedIn or by sending an email to x.w.devries@tilburguniversity.edu
